preferred-citation:
  type: article
  title: "A Dual-Track Framework for GLP-1 Side Effect Estimation: Separating Clinical Evidence from Real-World Patient Reports"
  authors:
    - family-names: Goyal
      given-names: Saurabh
      email: saurabh@magistra.health
      affiliation: "Magistra Health B.V."
  year: 2026
  month: 4
  url: "https://magistra.health/en/methodology"
  abstract: "Patients starting GLP-1 receptor agonist therapy face a persistent information gap: clinical trial side effect frequencies often diverge substantially from the experiences described in patient communities, but existing resources typically report only one or the other. We describe a dual-track estimation framework that collects, extracts, and reports two parallel risk estimates per side effect—one derived exclusively from peer-reviewed clinical trial and regulatory data, the other from real-world patient community reports—without blending them."
